A team from Facebook, led by its Head of Public Policy Africa, Ebele Okobi today paid a courtesy visit to the National Information Technology Development Agency (NITDA) Corporate Head Office in Abuja. The visit was neccesitated by the need to collaborate with the Agency to deepen penetration of internet connectivity across Nigeria with the aim of driving economic diversity and empowering Tech entrepreneurs for wealth creation. Okobi revealed that Facebook was attracted to Nigeria due to her favourable policy environment and called for a combined effort with the Agency to checkmate individuals using the platform to disseminate hate speeches. In his remarks, the Director General of NITDA, Dr Isa Ali Ibrahim Pantami, FBCS commended the platform for its initiative to support Nigeriaâ€™s tech entrepreneurs, small and medium scale businesses towards achieving success. <img src="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/FB_IMG_1519394242126-420x280.jpg" alt="" width="420" height="280" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-58839" srcset="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/FB_IMG_1519394242126-420x280.jpg 420w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/FB_IMG_1519394242126-150x100.jpg 150w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/FB_IMG_1519394242126-768x512.jpg 768w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/FB_IMG_1519394242126-720x480.jpg 720w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/FB_IMG_1519394242126.jpg 810w" sizes="(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px" /> Dr Pantami then called on Facebook to work more on putting measures in place to checkmate impersonation of accounts citing himself as an example of being a victim of account impersonation severally. A.M Tanimu is an Online Editor with Africa's Largest TV Network. With a decade experience in Television journalism, and a graduate of University of Maiduguri. Tanimu also produces TV shows with NTA when not on Social media.